                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.10434/2605.10434v1/x4.png",
                "caption": "Figure 4:Qualitative comparison on representative reasoning cases.Visually plausible generations can still fail process-level world reasoning, while higher-scoring models better preserve the intended state transition and temporal dynamics.",
                "position": 1257
            }
